data.content:
The `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` 10.0 package upgraded from **OpenAPI.NET v1 to v2**, which restructured the object model significantly. Here are the breaking changes in your code:

## 1. `OpenApiAny` types removed
`OpenApiString`, `OpenApiInteger`, etc. are gone. Use native `JsonNode`:

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;

param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

## 2. `OpenApiResponse` → use `OpenApiResponse` but `Responses` is now a dictionary of `OpenApiResponse`
The `Responses` collection changed to `IDictionary<string, OpenApiResponse>`. This part likely still compiles, but verify the namespace.

## 3. `OpenApiReference` restructured
`ReferenceType` enum and inline `Reference` property were replaced. Security schemes are now referenced by ID string directly:

```csharp
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
{
    Reference = new OpenApiReference { Id = "oauth2" }
};
```
`Type` on `OpenApiReference` is removed — it's inferred from context.

## 4. `Schema.Nullable` removed
OpenAPI v3.1 (which v2 of the library targets) dropped `nullable`. Use the `type` keyword array instead:

```csharp
property.Value.Type = property.Value.Type & ~JsonSchemaType.Null; // remove nullable
// or to add nullable:
// property.Value.Type = property.Value.Type | JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

## Fixed code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses ??= new Dictionary<string, OpenApiResponse>();
    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
    {
        Reference = new OpenApiReference { Id = "oauth2" }
    };
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type = property.Value.Type & ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

**Summary of changes:**
| .NET 9 (OpenAPI.NET v1) | .NET 10 (OpenAPI.NET v2) |
|---|---|
| `new OpenApiString("x")` | `JsonValue.Create("x")` |
| `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` | `using System.Text.Json.Nodes` |
| `ReferenceType.SecurityScheme` | Removed — inferred from context |
| `schema.Nullable = false` | `schema.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null` |
